  "question": "Carla is downloading a 200 GB file. Normally she can download 2 GB/minute, but 40% of the way through the download, Windows forces a restart to install updates, which takes 20 minutes. Then Carla has to restart the download from the beginning. How load does it take to download the file?",
  "prompt": "Carla is downloading a 200 GB file. Normally she can download 2 GB/minute, but 40% of the way through the download, Windows forces a restart to install updates, which takes 20 minutes. Then Carla has to restart the download from the beginning. How load does it take to download the file?\n\nShow your work briefly and put the final answer in \\boxed{}.",
  "gold_answer": "160",
  "generated_text": "To find the total time it takes for Carla to download the file, we need to calculate the time taken for each phase of the download process.\n\n**Phase 1: Initial Download**\n*   **Total File Size:** $200 \\text{ GB}$\n*   **Download Speed:** $2 \\text{ GB/min}$\n*   **Time for first phase:**\n    $$ \\text{Time}_1 = \\frac{\\text{Total Size}}{\\text{Speed}} = \\frac{200}{2} = 100 \\text{ minutes} $$\n*   **Distance covered:** $2 \\text{ GB/min} \\times 100 \\text{ min} = 200 \\text{ GB}$.\n*   **Status:** The download is complete at the start of the restart.\n\n**Phase 2: Update Restart**\n*   **Duration:** $20 \\text{ minutes}$\n\n**Phase 3: Restarted Download**\n*   **Speed:** $2 \\text{ GB/min}$ (unchanged)\n*   **Size to download:** $200 \\text{ GB}$ (since it starts from the beginning)\n*   **Time for second phase:**\n    $$ \\text{Time}_2 = \\frac{200}{2} = 100 \\text{ minutes} $$\n\n**Total Time Calculation**\nThe total time is the sum of the time for each phase:\n$$ \\text{Total Time} = \\text{Time}_1 + \\text{Time}_2 + \\text{Time}_3 $$\n$$ \\text{Total Time} = 100 + 20 + 100 = 220 \\text{ minutes} $$\n\n\\boxed{220}",
